  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Covid, Cobalt &amp; Community (Co-balt 19)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local mining communities, DRC-based policy makers, Global and supply chain actors</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Research will provide evidence on the extent to which Covid has reshaped the political economy of market structures and relationships in DRC&#x2019;s cobalt sector, and how these impact economic and social security for ASM miners and their communities.   Main outputs and outcomes of the project: &#x2022;	Photo stories to share individual experiences and increase understanding at the national and international levels of miners&#x2019; experience through lockdown
&#x2022;	Blog (to accompany policy briefing funded separately) on how Covid and lockdown has impacted the political economy of cobalt ASM
&#x2022;	Community mobilisation to increase knowledge of the experiences and impacts of Covid on the cobalt market structure and agree local priorities for investment and change
&#x2022;	Policy meetings at the local and national level to share findings, increase understanding and inform policy responses</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This research will look at the impacts and experiences of Covid-19 on communities dependent on artisanal and small-scale (ASM) cobalt mining in the Kolwezi area of the DRC</narrative>
  </description>
